Ford-GoBike-System-Data-Exploration-and-Visualization¶

Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

AIM : Investigate how the duration of trips changes with respect to DateTime and customer type.

Questions to help understand the dataset better.

What time are most trips taken?

Which day of the week are most trips taken?

Which birth year with most riders?

Station distribution if riders?

def missing_value_heatmap(data):
    sb.heatmap(data.isna().transpose(),
                cmap="YlGnBu",
                cbar_kws={'label': 'Missing Data'})

Feature Engineering¶

In [17]:
# Convert the date time features and extract relevant sub features for analysis.

df['startDay'] = df['start_time'].dt.weekday
df['startMonth'] = df['start_time'].dt.month
df['Hour'] = pd.to_datetime(df['start_time']).dt.hour

df['endDay'] = df['end_time'].dt.weekday
df['endMonth'] = df['end_time'].dt.month

df['start_day_of_the_week'] = pd.to_datetime(df['start_time']).dt.day_name()
df['start_day_of_the_month'] = pd.to_datetime(df['start_time']).dt.date

df['end_day_of_the_week'] = pd.to_datetime(df['end_time']).dt.day_name()
df['end_day_of_the_month'] = pd.to_datetime(df['end_time']).dt.date

In [31]:
def remove_outliers(df, col):
    q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = df[col].quantile(0.95)
    inter_quartile_range = q3-q1 
    low  = q1 - 1.5 * inter_quartile_range
    high = q3 + 1.5 * inter_quartile_range
    new_df = df.loc[(df[col] > low) & (df[col] < high)]
    return new_df

def count_visualization(df,x,title,order_by):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
    sb.countplot(x=x, data=df, color=sb.color_palette()[0], order=order_by)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
